reviews.text: Nice old station for trainspotting. Again, old rural station with original features with a light 70s refurbishment

Not much to be expected from this station. Facilities are absolutely rubbish with barely any seating and shelter provided on the platforms and a ticket office staffed in the early weekday mornings. It's good for watching trains and it has a large car park too. Other than that, rubbish station.

reviews.text: Milford is located in the town with the same name and is used by Southwest Trains, Milford is one of the worst stations I have seen here is why, the station display screens do not always display proper arrival times of trains. The station isn't clean thus gives off an unpleasant aroma, not a lot of trains stop here and the area has a bit of noise, the loo is always closed, station equipment is always breaking, the station is outdated, signs are barely able to be read properly, and the station isn't staffed, that is why this station isn't suitable for passenger use. Please use Haslemere or Goldamin instead of this station!!!
